<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A six-month-old chocolate labrador named Coco has died after she was found with a fractured skull in the backyard when her horrified owner returned from work.</p>

<p>Coco's owner returned to their house in Cobbadah Place in Freshwater in Sydney's Northern Beaches on Tuesday afternoon to find the puppy unresponsive.</p>

<p>The labrador was rushed to the vet after being found laid across the garden, but later died from her devastating head injuries.</p>

<p>A six-month-old labrador was found with severe head injuries in a backyard at a home in Freshwater, on Sydney's Northern Beaches (stock image)</p>

<p>X-rays confirmed Coco had a damaged skull as NSW Police investigate the death.</p>

<p>Dog owners have been warned about the incident and police are urging the public to come forward with any information. </p>

<p>Anyone with information is urged to call Dee Why Police or crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000. </p>

<p>RSPCA NSW has been contacted for comment.  </p>
